programme.title: Tragic Commitment
programme.desc: Alex is happily married to a gynecologist, Tung for five years. When Alex is fatally wounded in an accident, he feels obliged to tell Tung about his affair with Blackie.

programme.title: The Merry Wife

programme.title: Clan Of Amazons
programme.desc: This roadside robber embroiders flowers on handkerchiefs to leave at the scene of his crime, and not only steals from the rich, but blinds them!

programme.title: Gossip Street
programme.desc: The place to be is flat number 8 on the second floor of the Gossip Street apartment building, where neighbors gather to gossip. The sitcom turns serious when a local mobster wants to change the place into a gambling den.

programme.title: The Black Falcon
programme.desc: Newcomer Jenny Hu and veteran Margaret Tu Chuan unite onscreen to battle against a notorious Singaporean crime syndicate, facing fire, forgery and poisoned needles along the way!

programme.title: Puppy Love
programme.desc: This is a story of adolescent playfulness and innocence lost. Two best friends grow up together, but rivalry intervenes when they discover boys!

programme.title: Ambush
programme.desc: Ambush sees officer of the law Wan Chao Fan and his father being framed for a robbery they did not commit.

programme.title: Love With The Perfect Stranger
programme.desc: After breaking up with his girlfriend, salesman Bao meets a rich girl, Jin Jin, who just broke up with her boyfriend. Two equally heartbroken strangers fall in love instantly and get married on impulse.

programme.title: The Black Butterfly
programme.desc: Waitress Kwan leads a double life as moralistic outlaw, Black Butterfly. When she steals a cache of gold from the Five Devils Rock bandits, she soon has the government on her tail.

programme.title: My Name Ain't Suzie
programme.desc: Young Mei Li works as a bar girl in Wanchai to make a living. When she meets Jimmy in the bar, she thinks he is her true love and falls crazily in love with him. When Jimmy has to leave, Mei Li is devastated.

programme.title: Heroes Of The East
programme.desc: After marrying into a Japanese martial arts family, our Chinese hero inadvertently insults them all, leading to a number of stand-offs as he must fight to defend Chinese kung-fu.

programme.title: The Last Tempest
programme.desc: This sequel to The Empress Dowager continues the tale of Emperor Guangxu and Empress Dowager Cixi. Despite Guangxu's enthronement, his ability to rule effectively is overshadowed by the ever-present power of Cixi.

programme.title: The King Boxer
programme.desc: This tale of a honorable fighter's retraining in the 'Iron Palm' style, that became the first international martial arts movie hit and made a continent-spanning star of Lo Lieh.

programme.title: When The Clouds Roll By
programme.desc: A schizophrenic who refuses to believe her pilot lover was killed and believes his death to be a lie created to end their relationship.

programme.title: The New One-Armed Swordsman
programme.desc: David Chiang leaps into action as all-new one-armed hero when the love of his life is kidnapped and his best friend is murdered by a gang hiding out on Tiger Mountain.

programme.title: The Bride Napping
programme.desc: A rich girl Yue Ying, together with her maid Chun Lan, encounter a poor scholar Bian Ji at a fete. Chun Lan realizes Yue Ying is in love with him, but mixes his identity with a bandit due to an old servant's confusion.

programme.title: The Invincible Fist
programme.desc: A dedicated chief constable nicknamed 'The Invincible Fist' is chasing after a band of bandits near a village one day and encounters an innocent blind girl.

programme.title: The Singing Escort
programme.desc: The music and magic of The Singing Escort is a great showcase for Betty Ting Pei's on-screen appeal. Ting playing Susan, a young woman hiding from her father.

programme.title: Golden Swallow
programme.desc: A heroine finds herself in a love triangle with a swordsman and a warrior. They team up to conquer the evil forces of the martial arts world.

programme.title: The Big Sting
programme.desc: Three buddies find a rare artifact known as the Double-Faced God but are poisoned by Lady Wu who steals the treasure from them. Before they die, they get their wives to promise to train their children to take it back.

programme.title: Four Riders
programme.desc: Four martial arts experts live in Seoul after the Korean War in the 1950s. One of them inexplicably crosses path with a drug trafficking syndicate, and his three friends have no choice but to fight on his side.

programme.title: Love Without End
programme.desc: Lin Dai stars as a nightclub singer who falls for a young architect. When he suffers grave financial difficulty, she does the unthinkable to help him.

programme.title: The Spiritual Boxer
programme.desc: Wang Yu is a fake ghost catcher whose deficient skills make him ill-equipped to fend off the irritable townsfolk. When he doublecrosses a local gangster, he is forced to fight.

programme.title: Mist Over Dream Lake
programme.desc: Yen Chun directs and stars in a heartwarming drama about a young girl, Chen whose parents send her to a relative's farm for an unforgettable summer.

programme.title: Duel For Gold
programme.desc: Three pairs of cunning male and female crooks trying to steal a million gold taels from the Fu Lai Treasury House.

programme.title: Forbidden Tales Of Two Cities
programme.desc: Amorous complications and modern morals are just the beginning in Macau, where a love quartet is the source for sexy merriment.

programme.title: The Mighty One

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung And The...
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung meets a famous courtesan in Suzhou and in order to spend as much time as possible with her, he builds a direct underground tunnel into the Forbidden City.

programme.title: Clan Of The White Lotus

programme.title: The Mirror And The Lichee
programme.desc: The curious title refers to two props that signal a happy beginning to what develops into a tragic love story between the scholar and a local beauty.

programme.title: Two Con Men
